Implement Profile metatype variable binding in tap handlers

DESCRIPTION:
Profile metatype variables (e.g., `p` in `| Profile p |>`) are not accessible
in tap handler invocations. Generated code fails with "use of undeclared identifier 'p'".

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA:
1. Profile variable 'p' accessible in handler: `logger(msg: p.source)`
2. Test passes with output: "[PROFILE] input:hello\n"
3. Profile provides: source, branch, destination, timestamp_ns

TEST DESIGN:
- Uses concrete source pattern (hello -> *) to isolate from wildcard issues
- Single metatype variable binding in simple handler invocation
- No wildcard patterns to avoid confusing root causes

ROOT CAUSE:
The metatype_binding transformation in koru_std/taps.kz (around line 441-487)
creates variable bindings but doesn't properly inject them into the generated
invocation context. The variable scope is lost during code generation.

SOLUTION APPROACH:
The metatype binding needs to:
1. Create the metatype struct from compiled metadata
2. Make it available in scope for the handler invocation
3. Ensure it survives through backend code generation
